'''MAX''' is a [[Linux distribution]] sponsored by the department of education of the [[autonomous community]] of [[Madrid]]. MAX stands for '''MA'''drid Linu'''X'''. It was formerly based on [[Knoppix]], while its last release, MAX 4.0, is based on [[Ubuntu (operating system)|Ubuntu]] 8.04 LTS. Since 2003 MAX has been installed on all the computers of the schools in the autonomous community of Madrid.{{Citation needed|date=August 2009}} MAX supports both [[KDE]] and [[GNOME]] along with most common programs used under Linux such as [[Konqueror]], [[Mozilla Thunderbird]], [[OpenOffice.org]], [[Mozilla Firefox]] and [[Audacity]]. MAX comes as both a [[Live DVD]] and an installable system, as well as a [[USB]] version.
Last release is 6.0 with [[multiseat configuration|multiseat]] support and configurable skin for primary education.
